Some of 247 pupils, who benefited from the 247 pairs of shoes from Mr A. Casanova. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories IT was a joyous moment for management, teachers, pupils and parents of Mount Ernestina Combined School when Mr A. Casanova donated 247 pairs of school shoes, valued at R25 000 to pupils in need. Greytonian Mr Casanova is totally committed to the importance of education for the youth and has given several generous donations to youngsters in need.and loves to see pupils developing through education. Spokesperson for Mount Ernestina told Greytown Gazette that the donation was a blessing and greatly appreciated by the school, especially beneficiaries. The school has many pupils who come from disadvantaged families, and in are need of school uniforms, food, and so on. - Thanda Jila.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.